te most of his poetry, and of how his work represents, by dint of its linguistic character, an act of defiance and affirmation, in Delor's view, a 'metalinguistic literature'. D. GARETH WALTERS is Professor of Hispanic Studies at the University of Swansea.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aCatalan poetryxHistory and criticismy20th century. 4aHispanic Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Spanish & Portuguese.2bisacsh  a20th century literature.  aCatalan literature.  aFrancoism.  aSalvador Espriu.  aSpanish literature.  aThe Poetry of Salvador Espriu.  aaffirmation.  acivic.  acultural resistance.  adefiance.  adifficult poetry.  ahermetic poetry.  alinguistic character.  alyric.  ametalinguistic literature.  amoral resistance.  anumerology.  apoetry.  asymmetry.1 aWalters, D. Gareth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846154997423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846154997/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles